remarks.format:
## Remarks

`SKFourByteTag` encodes four ASCII characters into a single 32-bit unsigned integer. It is used throughout the font API to identify variation axes, OpenType features, and similar tagged values. Instances are implicitly convertible to and from `uint`.

## Examples

```csharp
// Create from individual characters
var tag = new SKFourByteTag('w', 'g', 'h', 't');

// Create from a string
var tag2 = SKFourByteTag.Parse("wght");

// Convert to string
Console.WriteLine(tag.ToString()); // "wght"
```
